shit: 2:1: warning: An echo of a command substitution prints what the command already prints.
     2 |  echo $(echo $(echo deep))
       |  ^~~~ here.
note: Run the command on its own instead.
shit: 2:6: warning: An unquoted command substitution splits its output.
     2 |  echo $(echo $(echo deep))
       |       ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ here.
note: Quote it to keep one argument.
shit: 2:6: warning: A command substitution wraps a useless echo.
     2 |  echo $(echo $(echo deep))
       |       ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ here.
note: The text can be used directly without the subshell.
